Write an if statement that checks if the value a lies in the range of 10 to 30 and
assigns the value of the variable a to 20.

if 10 <= a <= 30:
    a = 20

________________________________________________________________________________________
Write an if-else statement that assigns 0 to the variable b if the variable a is less
than 10. Otherwise, it should assign 99 to the variable b.

if a < 10:
    b = 0
else:
    b = 99

________________________________________________________________________________________
Write an if-else statement that asks the user to enter the speed at which he is driving.
If the speed is more than 50 print ‘Speed in limit’ , else print ‘Speed should be
checked’.

speed = float(input("What was your speed: "))

if speed > 50:
    print("Speed in limit")
else:
    print("Speed should be checked")

